1
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,830
汤姆 高兴你能到来
Tom, glad to see you made it.

2
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,880
我才不会错过
I wouldn't miss it.

3
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:09,920
国家气候学会 太空总署指挥
National Weather Institute, this is NASA Command.

4
00:03:10,010 --> 00:03:13,130
转移牧场一号人造卫星控制
Transferring control of satellite Gulf-001...

5
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,630
六秒后
... in six...

6
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,630
五 四
... five... four...

7
00:03:16,810 --> 00:03:18,390
输入来源密码
Do source code.

8
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,100
禁止使用 需用核准密码

9
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:25,600
输入现时使用密码
Enter current access code. Captains Trilling, Gilder...

10
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:32,790
转移完成

11
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:43,040
控制了 是我们的了
We got it. It's ours.

12
00:03:44,050 --> 00:03:45,160
请注意
Be advised...

13
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:49,040
接收到牧场一号卫星 谢谢
...we have received satellite Gulf-001. Thank you, Houston.

14
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:52,260
好了 且看它们有何本领
All right, let's see what she can do.

15
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:56,340
启动观察功能
Activating observation function.

16
00:03:57,270 --> 00:03:59,430
准备第二阶段
Setting for Stage 2.

17
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,850
这是什么?
What have we got here?

18
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:10,940
删除掉
Clean it up.

19
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:16,360
她转身了
Oh, my God, she's turning over!

20
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:20,990
增大整幅图像
Apply full-image enhancing.

21
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:27,960
好砘
Holy guacamole!

22
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:31,960
这东西有效
The damn thing works.

23
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:34,880
那该死的邓查维
That goddamn Travis Dane.

24
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:39,680
视像这么清晰目标系统定很好
If the optical circuits are this good, the targeting system must be great.

25
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:41,640
丹会喜欢的
Dane would love this.

26
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:44,980
太空总暑以为这是气象卫星
NASA thinks this is a weather satellite.

27
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:48,150
进行武器检查
Let's do a weapons check.

28
00:04:49,610 --> 00:04:52,150
这不是国会认为的浪费金钱
This wasn't the bust Congress thought it was.

29
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:55,160
国会不知道的事对我们没伤害
What Congress doesn't know won't hurt them, or us.

30
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:57,190
有不妥吗?
Something wrong, Captain?

31
00:04:57,290 --> 00:04:59,660
可惜丹今天不在这里
It's too bad Dane wasn't here today.

32
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:02,040
屈维斯丹是个疯子
Travis Dane was a nut.

33
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:04,410
他把车驶进湖里
He drove his car into a lake.

34
00:05:04,670 --> 00:05:06,000
他是疯的
He was crazy.

35
00:05:06,170 --> 00:05:07,170
找到尸体没有?
They find the body yet?

36
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:09,250
没有 只找到车
No, just the car.

37
00:05:09,460 --> 00:05:13,630
及写有『有志者事竟成』字条
And a note that said: "Chance favors the prepared mind."

38
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,000
奇怪吧?
Odd, huh?

39
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:18,010
丹也是怪的
But then, so was Dane.

40
00:05:18,850 --> 00:05:20,970
你们做得好
Captains, you did a hell of a job.

41
00:05:21,180 --> 00:05:23,060
该引以为傲
Be proud of yourselves.

42
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:24,640
周末愉快
Enjoy your weekend.

43
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:26,140
谢谢 将军
Thank you, General.

44
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:28,350
我可和你谈吗?失陪
Can I talk to you? Excuse me.

45
00:05:28,650 --> 00:05:30,190
周末愉快
Have a nice weekend.

46
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:32,360
回家去
Go home.

47
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:36,360
周末空军学院有航空展
There's an air show at the Air Force Academy this weekend.

48
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:39,400
要和我去吗?
Maybe you'd like to join me for a drink?

49
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:42,700
研究新的技技
Check out the new technologies.

50
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:46,410
高层军官会出席 很难说
All the top brass will be there. Who knows...

51
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,830
会对你的事业有助
...it might help your career.

52
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:51,420
抱歉 我有节目
Sorry, I have plans.

53
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:54,040
好的 我明白
Yeah, sure, I understand.

54
00:05:54,130 --> 00:05:56,380
一如将军所说
Like the General said...

55
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,720
你做得好
...you did a good job.

56
00:05:59,930 --> 00:06:01,210
过奖
Thank you...

57
00:06:01,770 --> 00:06:03,050
长官
...sir.

58
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:18,310
快点 你迟到了
Let's go, you're running late.

59
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,660
你去了哪儿?
Where have you been?

60
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:31,330
有特别任务?
On a special op?

61
00:06:32,010 --> 00:06:33,800
很荣幸
Lieutenant, always a pleasure.

62
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:36,010
我知道 你不能对我说
I know, you can't tell me.

63
00:06:37,220 --> 00:06:39,260
很抱歉关于你哥哥的事
Sorry to hear about your brother.

64
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:41,090
我也很难过
Me, too.

65
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:46,220
得赶上火车 它45分钟后开行
We must hurry to make that train. It leaves in 45 minutes.

66
00:06:46,730 --> 00:06:49,180
你们为何坐火车到加州
Why are you two taking a train to California?

67
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:51,680
她的父母因飞机失事去世
Would you fly if your parents died in a plane crash?

68
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:53,230
凯西
Hi, Casey.

69
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:58,610
这儿比你主持时好多了 我能搞定 可是
This place runs better when you're here. I can run it, but...

70
00:06:58,780 --> 00:07:00,240
你不懂烹饪
You can't cook.

71
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:04,030
顾客为你而非为我才来光顾
The patrons come here for you, Casey, not for me.

72
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:10,120
可爱的孩子
She's a cute kid.

73
00:07:10,460 --> 00:07:13,750
这是你的侄女?   是的 是我唯一亲人
- Is that your niece? - Yes. She's the only family I have left.

74
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:16,660
我不知是否认得她
I don't know if I'll recognize her.

75
00:07:19,180 --> 00:07:21,340
快点 否则错过了火车
Come on, we'll miss that train.

76
00:07:21,970 --> 00:07:24,340
我错过兄长的葬礼 所以
I missed my brother's funeral, so...

77
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,350
我们不会错过火车
...we won't miss the train.

78
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:29,140
请注意
Your attention, please.

79
00:07:29,230 --> 00:07:34,730
由丹佛往麻省列车现在登车
The Grand Continental Service from Denver to Los Angeles, now boarding.

80
00:08:13,610 --> 00:08:16,610
莎拉雷贝克有拿车票吗?
Has a Sarah Ryback picked up any tickets?

81
00:08:16,860 --> 00:08:18,600
凯西叔叔
Uncle Casey.

82
00:08:20,490 --> 00:08:22,110
很高兴看见你
Nice to see you, too.

83
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:24,280
你亭亭玉立了
You've gotten big.

84
00:08:24,370 --> 00:08:26,530
五年的变化会很大
A lot can happen in five years.

85
00:08:27,350 --> 00:08:29,710
等一等
Just a moment.

86
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:32,540
最近在忙些什么?
So, what have you been doing?

87
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:38,430
处理飞机失事 葬礼等事
Taking care of airplane crashes, funerals, stuff like that.

88
00:08:38,630 --> 00:08:40,620
是的 那么
Yeah, so...

89
00:08:41,010 --> 00:08:42,920
行了 三号月台
Here you are. Track 3.

90
00:08:56,230 --> 00:08:58,140
我刚才在想
You know, I was thinking...

91
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:02,270
你以前收集玩具熊我给你买了
I remembered that you collect teddy bears and I got you one.

92
00:09:02,410 --> 00:09:05,820
它不及你部份的藏品
It isn't as good as some of yours...

93
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,570
你亦可能太成熟
...and I know you may be too mature...

94
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:11,160
不会再玩玩具熊了
...to hang out with teddy bears now.

95
00:09:11,870 --> 00:09:14,030
但主要的是心意
It's the thought that counts.

96
00:09:14,170 --> 00:09:15,250
谢谢
Thanks.

97
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:21,500
这方面我倒没有受训
I guess I'm not trained for this.

98
00:09:24,890 --> 00:09:26,430
请问
Excuse me.

99
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:31,180
我可替你拿行李吗?不错的
Can I carry your bags? Oh, nice...

100
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:33,770
奖章
...medal you got there.

101
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:35,180
是海军十字动章
It's a Navy Cross.

102
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:37,980
我叔叔是海军但他没你帅
My uncle was in the Navy, but he didn't look like you.

103
00:09:38,070 --> 00:09:40,110
这是什么?
- What is that? - This?

104
00:09:40,190 --> 00:09:41,470
喷雾防身器
It's Mace.

105
00:09:41,860 --> 00:09:46,190
我要假装忙着让我替你拿行李吧
All right. Listen, I have to look busy, so why don't you let me take your bag?

106
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:48,190
否则我会给辞退
If I don't, I could get fired.

107
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:52,370
这样我便没钱念大学 我会穷
If I get fired, I won't have enough money for college, and I'll be poor.

108
00:09:53,210 --> 00:09:55,450
这样可以了 我喜欢
This will work. I like this.

109
00:09:55,630 --> 00:09:58,120
你说你在哪一个车厢?
What compartment did you say you were in?

110
00:09:58,550 --> 00:10:00,210
我的车厢
My compartment.

111
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,700
吉尔上尉
Captain Gilder...

112
00:11:12,870 --> 00:11:14,700
很高兴看见你
...fancy meeting you here.

113
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:17,990
顺林上尉 喝香槟吧
Have some champagne, Captain Trilling.

114
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:26,210
等候的人会有好东西
Good things come to those who wait.

115
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:31,710
你已等得够久了
Okay, you waited.

116
00:13:39,020 --> 00:13:43,140
不知那边的女孩子喝些什么
I was wondering what that girl over there is drinking.

117
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:47,190
那个喝莱姆汽水的女孩吗?
The little girl with the tonic and lime and the bad ID?

118
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,640
正是那一个
That's the one.

119
00:13:54,780 --> 00:13:56,860
你不喝酒?
- You're not drinking? - No.

120
00:13:57,700 --> 00:14:00,030
和我一起喝 我不喜欢独个儿喝
Join me. I don't like drinking alone.

121
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,490
你的饮料没有酒
There's no alcohol in that.

122
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:08,210
反正你什么也知道
Yeah, you always knew everything, anyway.

123
00:14:08,710 --> 00:14:12,500
我们可以聊点轻松点的吗?
Do you think we could have a pleasant conversation?

124
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,000
可以
Sure.

125
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:18,510
谈谈你和我爸为何不讲话吧
Let's talk about why you and my dad stopped talking.

126
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,720
听着
Listen...

127
00:14:21,810 --> 00:14:25,890
我知道你父亲和我意见不合
...I know that your father and I had our differences...

128
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:30,150
但我爱他
...but that doesn't mean I didn't love him.

129
00:14:30,230 --> 00:14:31,980
你没不和他说话
But you didn't even talk.

130
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:36,570
那是很久以前
Time goes by...

131
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:40,570
时光飞逝 不知不觉间
...it seems to fly, and before you know it...

132
00:14:41,290 --> 00:14:42,780
事情发生了
...things happen.

133
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:47,580
但我从没想过
But I never thought...

134
00:14:48,710 --> 00:14:52,160
我会没机会把事情说清楚
...I'd never get a chance to straighten things out with him.

135
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,330
你知道
You know...

136
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:59,000
他在并不是好惹的人
...he didn't get the medals in the service by being a choirboy.

137
00:15:01,430 --> 00:15:04,350
别这样子说我爸爸
I don't want you talking about my father that way.

138
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,230
我要喝酒
I need a drink.

139
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,400
有什么是最烈的?
What's the strongest stuff you got?

140
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:20,610
波多黎各甜酒如何?
How about Puerto Rican Rum?

141
00:15:25,580 --> 00:15:27,120
凯西叔叔
Uncle Casey...

142
00:15:27,660 --> 00:15:30,030
我不想争吵
I don't want to fight.

143
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:36,100
我到这儿前答应自己要把感受说
I just promised myself before I got here, that I would tell you how I felt.

144
00:15:37,010 --> 00:15:38,170
现在
Now...

145
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:40,340
我们做朋友吧
...let's just be friends.

146
00:15:42,890 --> 00:15:44,170
好的
Okay.

147
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:46,470
我到处走走
I'm going for a walk.

148
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:04,110
里面是什么?
- What's up? - What's in there?

149
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:07,790
是高度机密 我不能让你进去
It's top secret. I can't let you get in there.

150
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:08,740
里面是些什么?
What's in there?

151
00:16:08,830 --> 00:16:12,880
别迫我出手制止你 我有练举重
Don't make me restrain you, because I've been working out, see?

152
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,250
我轻易制服你
It'd be easy to do that.

153
00:16:15,340 --> 00:16:16,880
好的 制服我吧
Okay. Restrain me.

154
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:19,300
你要我这样?
You want me to?

155
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:20,330
是的
Yeah.

156
00:16:20,470 --> 00:16:23,670
好吧 这很容易
All right, if you say so. It'll be real easy.

157
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:31,820
里面有拖把
There's a mop...

158
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:35,720
扫扫以及许多发臭的东西
...a broom and a lot of smelly stuff you want to avoid.

159
00:16:39,030 --> 00:16:40,570
谁教你的?
Who taught you that?

160
00:16:40,660 --> 00:16:44,980
我十一岁时叔叔教我自卫技
When I was 11 years old, my uncle taught me all this neat stuff.

161
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:47,700
和你一起的那个人?
That's the dude that's with you?

162
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:49,700
是的
Yeah...

163
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:51,370
我猜是的
...I guess.

164
00:16:57,670 --> 00:16:58,950
我亦可以
I can do that.

165
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:06,470
你在写什么?
What are you writing?

166
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:10,020
是本书 我的回忆录
It's a book. My memoirs, stuff like that.

167
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:13,730
你这么年轻便写回忆录?
Aren't you too young to be writing your memoirs?

168
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:21,320
我知不合规矩但给我喝杯酒吧
I know it's against the rules, but give me a shot of something.

169
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:23,610
你可否把它们放上去?
Can you put those up there?

170
00:17:24,070 --> 00:17:25,110
可以
Yeah.

171
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:28,910
你的李小龙侄女怎么回事了?
What's up with that niece of yours, Miss Bruce Lee?

172
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,790
她差点杀了我
She almost killed me.

173
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:33,080
上!
Up!

174
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:36,250
是你教她的?
You taught her all that shit?

175
00:17:36,630 --> 00:17:38,420
只教了她一点点
I taught her a few things.

176
00:17:38,510 --> 00:17:40,790
还好她是女孩子
She's lucky she's a girl.

177
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:43,330
我也懂功夫的
I know some of that stuff myself.

178
00:17:43,430 --> 00:17:44,920
我听说了
That's what I hear.

179
00:17:45,050 --> 00:17:47,720
是我听你说的
Usually from you, but that's what I hear.

180
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:51,550
别给他白兰地 我要用来做蛋糕
Don't give him the brandy. I need it for the cake.

181
00:17:58,650 --> 00:17:59,900
看看
Look at that.

182
00:17:59,980 --> 00:18:03,730
因为火车摇动我的手法欠流畅
Because the train is rocking, it's cramping my style.

183
00:18:03,910 --> 00:18:08,120
我做给莎拉吃的 她最爱吃的
I'm making this for Sarah because it's her favorite thing.

184
00:18:19,710 --> 00:18:21,870
高温烘十五分钟
Fifteen minutes, on high.

185
00:18:22,470 --> 00:18:24,130
其余的听天由命
The rest is up to God.

186
00:18:24,260 --> 00:18:26,930
去找莎拉吧 给她一个惊喜
Now, go find Sarah, and we'll surprise her.

187
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:34,430
是什么声音?
What was that?

188
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:36,230
那称为
It's called a...

189
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:37,730
高潮
...orgasm.

190
00:18:37,810 --> 00:18:41,150
似是雷管 列车一定是在无讯号
Sounds like torpedoes. We must be in dark territory.

191
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,150
是什么回事?
What the hell is this?

192
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:46,320
他们不是铁路局的人
They're not our guys.

193
00:18:56,330 --> 00:18:58,120
有什么事?
What's the trouble?

194
00:18:58,290 --> 00:18:59,840
是什么回事?
