The hostages.

384
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:20,540
我不想他们受伤害
I don't want them hurt.

385
00:34:26,550 --> 00:34:29,130
请你留心 彭先生
Now, pay close attention, Mr. Penn.

386
00:34:29,430 --> 00:34:33,760
我会把大灾难弄成似是小事一桩
I'm about to make the Bhopal disaster look like a Girl Scout picnic.

387
00:34:36,110 --> 00:34:37,680
在那儿 回来了
There. It's back.

388
00:34:38,110 --> 00:34:41,390
没什么的 是轻微出错 虚惊一场
You see, it's nothing. A minor glitch. False alarm.

389
00:34:44,990 --> 00:34:46,400
那是什么东西?
What the hell is that?

390
00:34:46,490 --> 00:34:49,280
毒气 化学火灾
Poison gas, chemical fire...

391
00:34:49,660 --> 00:34:52,700
方圆一百里内完全毁灭
...total devastation for a 100-mile radius.

392
00:34:52,910 --> 00:34:55,240
以千计的人会死去
Thousands of people are going to die.

393
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:57,920
你听着和依我吩咐做
Just listen and do what I say.

394
00:34:58,090 --> 00:34:59,550
掩护和隐藏
Cover and concealment...

395
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:01,790
你跟别人同样知道
...you know as much as anybody!

396
00:35:02,510 --> 00:35:03,340
脱下白色的外衣 是的
Right.

397
00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:10,710
你再碰我便会有麻烦
You touch me again, it's your ass.

398
00:35:10,810 --> 00:35:12,050
目标密码
Targeting codes.

399
00:35:12,140 --> 00:35:15,230
他们开始我们的次序
- They've started our targeting sequence. - It's arming.

400
00:35:15,310 --> 00:35:18,600
太荒妙 定是操作错误
This is nuts. There must be some kind of malfunction.

401
00:35:18,820 --> 00:35:20,890
它在别处受到控制
It's being controlled elsewhere.

402
00:35:21,820 --> 00:35:23,760
目标是中国
Oh, Jesus, the target's mainland China.

403
00:35:23,860 --> 00:35:26,610
不会吧!
Not China!

404
00:35:26,870 --> 00:35:28,280
不能瞄准核子国家
Not somebody nuclear.

405
00:35:28,370 --> 00:35:29,830
是什么回事?
What's going on?

406
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:41,790
天啊
Sweet Jesus!

407
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:44,040
它进入进取模式
She's into acquisition mode.

408
00:35:44,170 --> 00:35:45,880
把它关掉吧!
Somebody shut it down!

409
00:35:46,180 --> 00:35:47,800
他们辞退我
They fired me.

410
00:35:47,890 --> 00:35:48,750
夺去一切
Took everything.

411
00:35:48,850 --> 00:35:50,420
它准备命中东西
She's powering up for a hit.

412
00:35:50,510 --> 00:35:52,470
说这技技不需要
Said the technology wasn't essential.

413
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:53,260
炸了它!
Blow it!

414
00:35:53,350 --> 00:35:54,890
关掉它!
Shut it down!

415
00:35:56,310 --> 00:35:57,890
没反应
No response.

416
00:35:57,980 --> 00:35:59,970
他们要的 定会得到
They wanted it! They'll get it!

417
00:36:00,820 --> 00:36:05,080
执行

418
00:36:17,470 --> 00:36:18,830
有志者事竟成

419
00:36:18,970 --> 00:36:22,500
彭以前这样说
That's what Dane used to say.

420
00:36:23,550 --> 00:36:25,840
通知五角大厦的贝兹上将
Call Admiral Bates at the Pentagon.

421
00:36:27,010 --> 00:36:31,050
他在科罗拉多出席航空展
Admiral Bates is here in Colorado attending an air show.

422
00:36:32,010 --> 00:36:33,890
那立即要他前来
Then get him here, now.

423
00:36:47,820 --> 00:36:50,820
各位 你们看见它是有效的
Gentlemen, as you can see, it works.

424
00:37:08,090 --> 00:37:10,930
这是只此一次的机会
This is a one-time offer.

425
00:37:11,180 --> 00:37:14,430
五角大厦二百尺下的小裂缝
Two hundred feet below the Pentagon, is an itty-bitty crack...

426
00:37:14,510 --> 00:37:17,850
我提议把它加大加阔
...which I propose to make great, big and wide.

427
00:37:17,930 --> 00:37:21,270
在它上面的是核子反应器
Directly above it is a strike-hard nuclear reactor.

428
00:37:22,020 --> 00:37:23,850
但它承受不了攻击
It ain't hard enough.

429
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:26,430
我们消灭五角大厦
We'll take out the Pentagon...

430
00:37:26,610 --> 00:37:28,020
神
...and God...

431
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:29,270
真主
...Allah...

432
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:31,110
若风向对的话
...and the wind's willing...

433
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:34,360
会遍及华府及东岸大部份地区
...Washington and most of the Eastern Seaboard as well.

434
00:37:45,380 --> 00:37:46,870
费用:
The fee:

435
00:37:47,210 --> 00:37:49,370
十亿元
One billion dollars.

436
00:37:49,550 --> 00:37:51,460
十亿元?
A billion dollars.

437
00:37:53,970 --> 00:37:55,460
我欠别人钱
I owe people money.

438
00:37:55,970 --> 00:37:57,000
糟了
Oh, shit.

439
00:37:57,140 --> 00:37:58,880
这是什么地方?
What is this place?

440
00:37:58,980 --> 00:37:59,890
我们要有准备
Here we go.

441
00:37:59,980 --> 00:38:03,180
我不知道 国会亦不知
- I don't know, nor does Congress. - Who's paying for it?

442
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:05,390
是什么回事?
What the hell is going on?

443
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:08,690
别说它是个气象站
Don't say this is just a weather station.

444
00:38:08,820 --> 00:38:10,530
显示在屏幕上
Bring the rendering up.

445
00:38:10,650 --> 00:38:14,700
我们把分子光束武器送上轨迹
Recently we deployed a particle-beam weapon into orbit.

446
00:38:14,910 --> 00:38:16,490
说简单一点
In English, please.

447
00:38:16,660 --> 00:38:21,070
需要许多钱 分子光束技技
It's a major cash cow. Particle-beam technology, it's the earthquake deal.

448
00:38:21,330 --> 00:38:23,870
以我所知已终止了那计划
It's my understanding we shut that program down.

449
00:38:23,970 --> 00:38:27,660
我们加以资助
We financed it.

450
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:29,250
贝克
Breaker, what?

451
00:38:30,260 --> 00:38:32,630
这东西发挥效用了?
This goddamn thing works now?

452
00:38:32,970 --> 00:38:34,790
它效能极好
It works so effectively...

453
00:38:34,890 --> 00:38:38,970
若瞄准罗省地震断层 十五秒后
...that if we targeted the Los Angeles fault lines, in 15 seconds...

454
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:42,060
亚历桑那会变成滨海地区
...Arizona would be beachfront property.

455
00:38:42,140 --> 00:38:45,010
问题是 别人指挥了卫星
The problem is, someone else is commanding the satellite.

456
00:38:45,110 --> 00:38:47,680
我们无法找到或摧毁它
We couldn't find it or destroy it...

457
00:38:48,650 --> 00:38:50,940
所以我们不可以阻止它
...so we were unable to stop it.

458
00:38:51,190 --> 00:38:52,650
天啊!
Oh, my God!

459
00:38:52,990 --> 00:38:54,150
中国的地震?
China's earthquake?

460
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:56,150
我们可完全否认
We have full deniability.

461
00:38:56,370 --> 00:38:57,530
糟透!
Shit!

462
00:38:57,620 --> 00:38:59,030
那是典型作风
That's typical.

463
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:02,700
中情局作风 你知对手是谁吗?
Typical Agency bullshit! Do you know who we're dealing with?

464
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:07,170
是设计这系统的邓查维
We think it's Travis Dane, the guy who designed the system.

465
00:39:07,420 --> 00:39:09,130
我们的人?
- One of our people? - Not anymore.

466
00:39:09,210 --> 00:39:12,330
他给辞退了 上月他自杀身亡
He was decommissioned. Last month he was an apparent suicide.

467
00:39:12,420 --> 00:39:16,550
他很聪明 能干 但神经病
He's brilliant. He can do anything he puts his mind to, but he's crazy.

468
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:19,300
你为何雇用狂徒?
Why would you hire a maniac?

469
00:39:19,390 --> 00:39:20,670
因为
Because...

470
00:39:21,060 --> 00:39:24,560
正常的人无法造出这样的武器
...sane people do not build weapons like this.

471
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:29,350
你认为我们可从中学习
You'd think we'd learn from that.

472
00:39:31,990 --> 00:39:34,270
好吧 把紧急状态提升
All right, we're upgrading to Code 3.

473
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:37,730
我们快找出那卫星及那杂种吧
Gentlemen, let's find the satellite, and the bastard, now!

474
00:40:13,780 --> 00:40:15,060
没有能量
No power.

475
00:40:20,200 --> 00:40:23,120
掩护和隐藏 你懂得的吧?
Cover and conceal. You know about that, right?

476
00:40:23,620 --> 00:40:25,530
你懂得这样做吧?
You know about that, right?

477
00:40:41,140 --> 00:40:44,010
我们有一客户有私事想求助
One of our customers has a small personal favor to ask.

478
00:40:44,430 --> 00:40:46,560
他想你炸毁一客机
He wants you to blow up an airplane.

479
00:40:46,640 --> 00:40:50,230
告诉他不行 我会炸五角大厦
Tell him to forget about it. I'm going to blow up the Pentagon.

480
00:40:50,310 --> 00:40:52,470
他不加入便无法参与
He either gets on board or gets left behind.

481
00:40:52,570 --> 00:40:56,100
但这人的前妻在这机上
But, sir, the gentleman's ex-wife is on board of this jet.

482
00:40:58,570 --> 00:41:00,130
请转告贝兹上将:

483
00:41:01,660 --> 00:41:04,580
他想你用为地下攻击设计的武器
He wants you to blow up a jet going 500 miles an hour...

484
00:41:04,660 --> 00:41:08,280
炸毁时速五百里的飞机?
...with a weapon designed for subterranean strikes?

485
00:41:08,670 --> 00:41:12,000
他说会额外给我们一亿元
He says he'll pay us an additional $100 million.

486
00:41:14,300 --> 00:41:15,290
真的?
Really?

487
00:41:16,090 --> 00:41:18,250
异频收发器的号码?
Do we have it's transponder numbers?

488
00:41:18,630 --> 00:41:20,130
他现时送来
Sending them now.

489
00:41:22,350 --> 00:41:23,380
我可办到
I can do this.

490
00:41:23,470 --> 00:41:26,840
钱存进我们的帐户他前妻便没命
His ex-wife is history once the money is in our account.

491
00:41:27,230 --> 00:41:29,430
一号会移至位置
Grazer One will be in position in...

492
00:41:30,850 --> 00:41:33,350
他有五分钟
He has five minutes to make the deposit.

493
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:37,960
里高餐室

494
00:41:39,370 --> 00:41:42,070
线路繁忙

495
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,660
钱已存入苏黎士
The money's hitting Zurich...

496
00:41:50,750 --> 00:41:51,530
对!
...now!

497
00:41:51,620 --> 00:41:53,780
好 开始
Good. Here we go.

498
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:02,630
牧场一号又回到银幕
Grazer's back on-line.

499
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:06,720
若他们联上我们便有麻烦
- lf they hooked up, we're in trouble. - Pegasus C Team is in range.

500
00:42:06,810 --> 00:42:10,390
B2轰炸机上有反卫星导弹
We have a B-2 bomber with two anti-satellite missiles on board.

501
00:42:16,570 --> 00:42:18,970
我以为你已截断下面的电源
I thought you cut the power downstairs.

502
00:42:21,810 --> 00:42:23,170
30秒后重发

503
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:51,560
战机导弹瞄准卫星听候你的命令
Pegasus locked on Grazer One. On your command.

504
00:42:51,730 --> 00:42:52,760
发射
Fire.

505
00:43:03,410 --> 00:43:05,280
我们可成功吗?
Can we get it before it fires?

506
00:43:05,370 --> 00:43:06,910
他们很慢
They are so slow.

507
00:43:23,220 --> 00:43:25,970
为何仍在数? 资料仍在传送
- Why is it counting? - Still getting the feed.

508
00:43:35,940 --> 00:43:38,260
空中地震
Earthquake in midair.

509
00:43:38,770 --> 00:43:41,560
我从没见过这么精彩的
That is the goddamnedest thing I've ever seen.

510
00:43:44,820 --> 00:43:47,280
我们击落了什么?
What the hell did we shoot down?

511
00:43:56,090 --> 00:43:58,580
21秒后重发

512
00:44:03,130 --> 00:44:07,430
若没有击落卫星我们击落什么?
I'll ask you again, if we didn't shoot down Grazer One, what did we shoot?

513
00:44:13,930 --> 00:44:16,310
到下面去看看赫拔
Check on Herb downstairs.

514
00:44:27,700 --> 00:44:30,370
已在传送中删去火车车声
Train noise eliminated from the transmission.

515
00:44:31,030 --> 00:44:33,030
我们准备致电老家吧
Let's get ready to call home.

516
00:44:33,370 --> 00:44:34,650
怎么了?
What's up?

517
00:44:34,910 --> 00:44:36,910
你哪里弄到枪的?
- Where'd you get the gun? - Get anything?

518
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:39,040
鱼杠 桌球棒 衣服
I got a fishing rod, pool cue and clothes.

519
00:44:39,130 --> 00:44:40,950
你是没用的浑蛋
You're a useless bastard.

520
00:44:41,040 --> 00:44:44,330
这是点四五的枪
Encrypted, no good. This is a.45, okay?

521
00:44:49,590 --> 00:44:54,670
左手 右手 掌心紧压一起
Dynamic tension, left hand, right hand, palms pressed together, okay?

522
00:44:54,850 --> 00:44:57,970
经常要攒前顾后 左看右望
Cover your ass, 12, 3, 6, 9, wherever you look always.

523
00:44:58,060 --> 00:45:01,850
枪指向那里便望那里 明白吗?
Never look in a direction where the gun ain't pointing, understand?

524
00:45:08,110 --> 00:45:09,740
那是谁?
Who the hell is that?

525
00:45:09,860 --> 00:45:11,410
主耶稣
Jesus Christ!

526
00:45:11,910 --> 00:45:15,860
我不是 虽然我从死里复活
Not quite, General Cooper, although I have sort of risen from the dead.

527
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:18,700
我只是你的老朋友屈维斯 丹
No, it's just your old friend, Travis Dane.

528
00:45:18,870 --> 00:45:21,540
你记得吗?给你辞退的人
You remember? The guy you fired!

529
00:45:22,040 --> 00:45:25,380
我相信你现时在问自己:
And I bet now you're probably asking yourselves:

530
00:45:25,630 --> 00:45:28,040
我们击落了什么?
"What the hell did we just shoot down?"

531
00:45:28,380 --> 00:45:29,500
答案是:
The answer is:

532
00:45:29,590 --> 00:45:34,050
国家安全机构唯一有效的卫星
The NSA's best and only functional real-time down-looking satellite...

533
00:45:34,350 --> 00:45:35,930
NSP一号
... the NSP-1.

534
00:45:36,100 --> 00:45:40,730
你可能查问他们有关卫星的用途
You'll probably be calling them any minute now, asking them for its use.

535
00:45:40,900 --> 00:45:44,350
可惜 由于他们不知它的下落
Unfortunately, since even they don't know where it is...

536
00:45:44,440 --> 00:45:45,980
亦无法帮你们
... they can't help you.

537
00:45:46,070 --> 00:45:47,530
查到他的下落吗?
Have you got him?

538
00:45:47,690 --> 00:45:49,070
快可以了
I'm closing in.

539
00:45:49,150 --> 00:45:52,520
你是知道上次在何处传送
You do know where the last transmission came from.

540
00:45:52,620 --> 00:45:54,770
你就可能查到
You're probably closing in fast...

541
00:45:54,990 --> 00:45:57,200
牧场一号的可能位置
... on Grazer One's probable location.

542
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:03,740
它就在某一处
It's in there somewhere...

543
00:46:03,960 --> 00:46:07,960
躲在我所创造的50枚假卫星中
... hiding among those 50 ghost satellites I've created...

544
00:46:08,470 --> 00:46:10,090
为你而造的
... just for you.

545
00:46:12,760 --> 00:46:14,470
那捞种死了
Motherfucker's gone.

546
00:46:16,470 --> 00:46:18,630
我的示范证明了
As my demonstration just proved...

547
00:46:19,100 --> 00:46:21,140
游牧者一号是可行的
... Grazer One is viable...

548
00:46:21,480 --> 00:46:23,640
亦能产生效果
... and can produce results.

549
00:46:23,810 --> 00:46:26,140
可再生的效果
Reproducible results.

550
00:46:26,610 --> 00:46:28,020
而为了证明
And to prove it...

551
00:46:28,110 --> 00:46:31,940
我会给你们再示范一次
... I'm going to give you another demonstration of my masterpiece.

552
00:46:32,280 --> 00:46:33,820
45分钟后
In 45 minutes...

553
00:46:34,160 --> 00:46:37,660
牧场一号到了发射的位置时
... as soon as Grazer One is in position for a clear shot...

554
00:46:38,080 --> 00:46:41,660
我会用九成八的威力炸五角大厦
... I'm going to hit the Pentagon with a 98 percent blast.

555
00:46:42,170 --> 00:46:46,630
可摧毁你们说并不存在的反应器
Enough to fracture the nuclear reactor you claim you don't have under there.

556
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:48,660
你这王八蛋
You son of a bitch.

557
00:46:48,840 --> 00:46:50,330
会有辐射性微尘
We'll have fallout.

558
00:46:50,510 --> 00:46:52,170
会有毁灭
We'll have devastation.

559
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:55,500
我有事情要办
I've got things to do.

560
00:47:00,810 --> 00:47:02,520
我要你们记着:
I want you to remember:

561
00:47:02,850 --> 00:47:05,890
我在上班前已比你们聪明
I was smarter than all of you before I worked there.

562
00:47:05,980 --> 00:47:09,070
受雇工作时亦比你们聪明
I was smarter than all of you while I worked there.

563
00:47:09,150 --> 00:47:11,480
我仍比你们聪明
And I'm still smarter than all of you.

564
00:47:11,610 --> 00:47:12,940
再见
Au revoir.

565
00:47:21,040 --> 00:47:23,990
他不是从这儿走否则我们会听到
He sure didn't go this way. We would've heard him.

566
00:47:24,920 --> 00:47:28,040
及时追查牧场一号下落的机会如
What are the odds of tracking Grazer down in time?

567
00:47:28,250 --> 00:47:30,540
我们该查询巴黎
We should check over Paris.

568
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:34,630
试想我们要函盖的范围
Considering the area we must cover...

569
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:36,540
因此它称为太空
That's why it's called "space."

570
00:47:36,640 --> 00:47:38,710
什么? 大声一点
What's that, son? Speak up.

571
00:47:39,970 --> 00:47:40,970
这个
